          <item>
    <title>Continuous Drupal deployment with Aegir, Git, and Jenkins</title>
    <link>http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/sessions/continuous-drupal-deployment-aegir-git-and-jenkins</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-userreference field-field-speakers&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a href=&quot;http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/users/notzach&quot; title=&quot;View user profile.&quot;&gt;Zach Seifts&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Put on your devops caps folks, I&#039;m going to talk about continuous deployment with &lt;a href=&quot;http://community.aegirproject.org/&quot;&gt;Aeigr&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://git-scm.com/&quot;&gt;Git&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;http://jenkins-ci.org/&quot;&gt;Jenkins&lt;/a&gt;. You&#039;ll be surprised how easy it can be to deploy code!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deployment scripts: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/zachseifts/aegir_deployment&quot;&gt;Aegir Deployment Scripts&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
