  <item>
    <title>Publishing with Drupal and distributing content with social media</title>
    <link>http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/sessions/publishing-drupal-and-distributing-content-social-media</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-userreference field-field-speakers&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a href=&quot;http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/users/jhibbets&quot; title=&quot;View user profile.&quot;&gt;Jason Hibbets&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How does a publication like opensource.com create and publish content with Drupal and then distribute with social media? This session will walk you through the intricate steps of our publishing process and provide tips and tricks on using social media to promote your Drupal content.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Questions answered by this session: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How does opensource.com create and gather content for their community?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How does opensource.com publish content?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to distribute content with social media, specifically, Facebook, Twitter, and Flickr.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How social media can be used on Drupal sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-audience&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-experience&quot;&gt;
