  <item>
    <title>Using node.js with Drupal</title>
    <link>http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/sessions/using-nodejs-drupal</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-userreference field-field-speakers&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a href=&quot;http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/users/jitesh-doshi&quot; title=&quot;View user profile.&quot;&gt;Jitesh Doshi&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://nodejs.org/&quot;&gt;node.js&lt;/a&gt; is a server-side technology that not only lets you code your server-side in JavaScript, but more importantly lets regular hardware scale to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kegel.com/c10k.html&quot;&gt;thousands of active concurrent connections&lt;/a&gt;. A beefy Drupal server can perhaps take that many sessions, but not that many &lt;strong&gt;active&lt;/strong&gt; connections.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This session will show you how to &lt;strong&gt;use node.js in conjunction with Drupal&lt;/strong&gt; so that you can send &lt;strong&gt;real time notifications&lt;/strong&gt; to ALL users on your site at the same time - initiated by the server.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This has many applications such as ...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sudden news flashes and broadcast messages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive chat with specific user(s)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Live play-by-play commentary of a game&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Live trading quotes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Live bidding in auctions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;... anything else you can imaging ...&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-audience&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-experience&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Intermediate        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
