  <item>
    <title>Bean Roasting: Creating block entities and writing plugins with the Bean module. </title>
    <link>http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/sessions/bean-roasting-creating-block-entities-and-writing-plugins-bean-module</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-userreference field-field-speakers&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a href=&quot;http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/users/brantwynn&quot; title=&quot;View user profile.&quot;&gt;Brant Wynn&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This presentation aims to help people get up and running using the Bean module.  (&lt;a href=&quot;http://drupal.org/project/bean&quot; title=&quot;http://drupal.org/project/bean&quot;&gt;http://drupal.org/project/bean&lt;/a&gt;)  Bean is an acronym that stands for Block Entities Aren&#039;t Nodes. Beans are fieldable, pluggable, reusable block entities. We will go over the basics of using the Bean UI and dive into code examples for writing custom Bean plugins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;	•	Overview of Entities in Drupal 7&lt;br /&gt;
	•	An Introduction to Bean and Bean UI&lt;br /&gt;
	•	Using View Modes with Bean &amp;amp; Entity View Modes&lt;br /&gt;
	•	Creating a reusable Bean with custom fields using the UI&lt;br /&gt;
	•	The PHP behind the Bean Example (Article Listing) Plugin Module&lt;br /&gt;
	•	Overview of code inside cool Bean plugin modules (i.e.:  Bean Relevant, Twitter Pull, Service Links)&lt;br /&gt;
	•	Interactive discussion about best practices for block configuration/placement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Much of this presentation will make use of code and walkthroughs within a working sandbox environment.  Slides, code snippets and screenshots will be used for some portions of the presentation as well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The goal is to provide a groundwork for where to start with Bean and encourage developers to write their own custom bean plugins. Attendees will walk away with a better understanding of Bean and its user interface. Those unfamiliar with Entities &amp;amp; View Modes in Drupal 7 may get an additional benefit from this course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-audience&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-experience&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Intermediate        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
</description>
