  <item>
    <title>SEO with Drupal 6 and Drupal 7</title>
    <link>http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/sessions/seo-drupal-6-and-drupal-7</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-userreference field-field-speakers&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a href=&quot;http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/users/david-minton&quot; title=&quot;View user profile.&quot;&gt;David Minton&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a href=&quot;http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/users/stephen-pashby&quot; title=&quot;View user profile.&quot;&gt;Stephen Pashby&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Overview:&lt;br /&gt;
In this session, we will discuss Drupal as a Search Engine Optimization (SEO) platform.&lt;br /&gt;
We will cover customizing your Drupal site to support your SEO efforts with specific advice for Drupal 6 and Drupal 7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will cover:&lt;br /&gt;
SEO Fundamentals: How SEO works and why you should care&lt;br /&gt;
Drupal and SEO: Drupal Core&#039;s default behavior for SEO and how you can augment it&lt;br /&gt;
SEO Best Practices for Drupal: How to train your content creators and site managers for SEO success&lt;br /&gt;
Drupal SEO Module Selection for Drupal 6 and Drupal 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Intended audience: Anyone with a Drupal site or is considering a Drupal site who is concerned about your placement in search engines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-schedule&quot;&gt;&lt;legend&gt;Schedule info&lt;/legend&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-nodereference field-field-session-slot&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
