  <item>
    <title>Use Display Suite, Make Fewer Custom Templates</title>
    <link>http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/sessions/use-display-suite-make-fewer-custom-templates</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-userreference field-field-speakers&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a href=&quot;http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/users/ultimike&quot; title=&quot;View user profile.&quot;&gt;Michael Anello&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Display Suite module is a wonderful way of customizing node (and any entity for that matter) templates through a drag-and-drop UI. You&#039;ll be amazed at how Display Suite elegantly extends what Drupal core provides site administrators when it comes to displaying entity content.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While not a replacement for the Panels module, Display Suite has clearly been influenced by it, and leverages its ideas in a new way. This presentation will only scratch the surface of what Display Suite is capable of - it will only focus on using it to provide alternate &quot;view modes&quot; for entities&#039; (nodes, users, taxonomy terms, etc...) display pages as well as demonstrating how it can be used to create new layouts (instead of having to create custom theme templates) for the same entities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-audience&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-experience&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Intermediate        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
</description>
     <comments>http://drupalcampcharlotte.com/sessions/use-display-suite-make-fewer-custom-templates#comments</comments>
